description.narrative: Ecuador CO strives to support the implementation of strategies that ensure the comprehensive, friendly and quality care of mother and child. UNICEF Ecuador focus its efforts in contributing towards the reduction of maternal and neonatal mortality rates, increasing breastfeeding rates and eliminating vertical transmission of HIV. This work was carried out under the umbrella of the Ecuadorian government led Mother and Baby Friendly Health Establishments (ESAMYN) strategy. Ecuador CO provides technical support in the implementation of this strategy at the local, institutional and structural level and in that contributing towards the improvement of maternal and neonatal health indicators. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
